22/02/2006
VIENNA, Austria -- The first direct talks between Belgrade and Pristina were held in a "co-operative spirit," Albert Rohan, the UN's deputy envoy for the talks, said on Tuesday (21 February). 
Negotiators found common ground on some issues under discussion, he added. 
The two sides are debating decentralisation issues and ways to transfer more powers to local governments in Kosovo. 
They agreed to meet again on 17 March. 
(Politika - 22/02/06; International Herald Tribune, FIFA.com, AP, AFP, Reuters, Tanjug, Beta, KosovaLive - 21/02/06)
